The Psychtoolbox Screen command passes control to a Screen subfunction which is specified when invoking Screen.  For example, Screen('OpenWindow',..) passes control to a C function which opens an onscreen window.   This documents  explains how to extend Screen by adding your own subfunctions.  \
\
Screen is used by programs written in the MATLAB language, but Screen itself and it's subfunctions are written in C.  This document assumes knowledge of C but no prior experience with Xcode.\
		\
Don't be intimidated by the number of steps listed here; We give details on how to control the Xcode interface which makes this explanation long in words though it is uncomplicated.\
